tourBios.carHigh: 2010: Missed the cut at the Nationwide Tour's Winn-Dixie Jacksonville Open in his only career Tour start.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the Seminole Collegiate tournament while at Florida State...Attended Huntington North High School in Indiana and Lakewood Ranch High School in Bradenton, FL.
tourBios.personal: Lists Bill Connely as an instructor...Says making it to the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament on his first try is his biggest thrill in golf and finishing 19 credits over the summer to graduate from Florida State is his biggest thrill outside of the game...Favorite course he's played is St. Andrews, and he would like to play Augusta National...Favorite college team is Florida State, and his favorite TV show is ESPN's "College Gameday." Favorite movie is "Tin Cup." Favorite athletes to watch are Michael Jordan and LeBron James...Favorite food is chicken. Favorite vacation spots are Hawaii and Colorado...Would round out his dream foursome with his father, Arnold Palmer and Jack Nicklaus...Says not many people know he can dunk a basketball...Has one older sister who played college basketball at Murray State.

tourBios.carHigh: 2015: T11 at the Canada Qualifying Tournament, firing scores of 70-73-72-69. Made five cuts in 12 starts with one top 10 and two top 25s. Was T2 at The Great Waterway Classic with rounds of 66-70-70-63. Moved up the leaderboard 32 spots Sunday thanks to a final-round 63...Posted T20 at the season-ending Freedom 55 Financial Championship in September.
tourBios.personal: Grew up on a small farm in Indiana...Previously worked in commercial insurance...Favorite course he's played is Winged Foot and wants to play Pebble Beach...Favorite pro sports' teams are the Tampa Bay Rays, Tampa Bay Lightning and Cleveland Cavaliers...Dream foursome would include his dad, Arnold Palmer and Tiger Woods.
